<p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Śrī Kaṇṭa Ī<supplied reason="lost">śvara</supplied>, a funerary temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paḷḷipaṭai</foreign></supplied> built <supplied reason="explanation"><supplied reason="lost"><foreign>e</foreign></supplied><foreign>ṭupiṭṭa</foreign></supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">Paḻu</supplied>veṭṭaraiyar Kaṇṭan Maṟavaṉā<supplied reason="lost">r</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> saying <supplied reason="explanation">eṉṟu</supplied>: “<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> is wanted <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>veṇṭum</foreign></supplied> to give <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tara</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>” <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> and we the lords <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kiḻavarōmum</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Śrī Kaṇṭa Ī<supplied reason="lost">śvara</supplied>, a funerary temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paḷḷipaṭai</foreign></supplied> built <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eṭupiṭṭa</foreign></supplied> by Aṭikaḷ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ār <supplied reason="explanation">?</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> gold <supplied reason="explanation">poṉṉum</supplied> and the <foreign>antarāyam</foreign>-tax <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>

